1
00:00:05,690 --> 00:00:12,902
Parents, they deal with children 
for a long time

2
00:00:12,902 --> 00:00:16,758
before a child
is able to express love.

3
00:00:16,943 --> 00:00:20,312
[Potency of Love]

4
00:00:20,573 --> 00:00:22,780
And in fact, 
in the very beginning

5
00:00:22,780 --> 00:00:24,340
you could make 
the opposite case:

6
00:00:24,340 --> 00:00:28,172
the child is
so self-absorbed,

7
00:00:29,130 --> 00:00:34,043
selfish, showing
many bad qualities,

8
00:00:34,501 --> 00:00:43,763
and only seeing parents 
as food suppliers and slaves.

9
00:00:44,582 --> 00:00:51,066
But they’re lovingly …
 

10
00:00:51,605 --> 00:00:55,243
they’re dealing with the child
in an affectionate way

11
00:00:55,243 --> 00:01:00,487
despite the absence 
of any genuine affection in the child,

12
00:01:00,487 --> 00:01:03,895
knowing that the child
has the capacity

13
00:01:03,925 --> 00:01:07,212
to express love
and affection in time.

14
00:01:07,582 --> 00:01:10,750
On the example when
Sanātan Goswāmī

15
00:01:10,750 --> 00:01:25,006
is feeling so distraught 
about having a physical disease,

16
00:01:25,006 --> 00:01:27,685
and Mahāprabhu’s embracing him,

17
00:01:27,685 --> 00:01:29,886
and some of that
is going on Mahāprabhu—

18
00:01:29,886 --> 00:01:32,069
it’s just unthinkable.

19
00:01:32,470 --> 00:01:39,165
And he’s thinking,
“I came here for spiritual upliftment

20
00:01:39,165 --> 00:01:45,460
and I’m going to Hell 
as a consequence

21
00:01:45,460 --> 00:01:49,497
of Mahāprabhu’s affection for me.”

22
00:01:49,497 --> 00:01:52,605
So he’s thinking 
he’ll maybe throw himself

23
00:01:52,605 --> 00:01:56,202
under the wheel 
of the rath of Jagannāth,

24
00:01:56,202 --> 00:01:59,154
he’s going 
to stop this somehow

25
00:01:59,246 --> 00:02:04,748
That’s when Mahāprabhu says:
sanātan, deha-tyāge kṛṣṇa nāhi paī—

26
00:02:04,757 --> 00:02:07,620
“You won’t get Kṛṣṇa by giving up the body.”
[Cc: 3.4.56]

27
00:02:07,621 --> 00:02:12,943
The body is just 
the outcome of the mind.

28
00:02:14,208 --> 00:02:17,797
Just by cutting away the body,
it doesn’t get rid

29
00:02:17,797 --> 00:02:21,264
of the root cause problem
of material existence,

30
00:02:21,264 --> 00:02:23,368
it only compounds it.

31
00:02:23,692 --> 00:02:26,861
So He said,
“That won’t get you Kṛṣṇa.”

32
00:02:27,616 --> 00:02:30,932
And they have 
different discussions,

33
00:02:31,485 --> 00:02:33,461
I mean Mahāprabhu says
different things,

34
00:02:33,461 --> 00:02:35,453
but one of the things 
He says:

35
00:02:35,453 --> 00:02:39,376
He talks about the mother
taking care of a baby,

36
00:02:39,376 --> 00:02:43,025
the baby’s pooping 
on the mother,

37
00:02:43,025 --> 00:02:47,806
and the mother’s thinking 
it’s like sandalwood paste.

38
00:02:47,806 --> 00:02:52,078
[Laughing]

39
00:02:52,078 --> 00:02:55,586
He said, so Mahāprabhu’s …
I mean … I’m just telling

40
00:02:55,586 --> 00:03:00,112
this is the actual stuff 
that’s in the books.

41
00:03:01,060 --> 00:03:03,251
It’s from the mouth of Mahāprabhu,
He says that.

42
00:03:03,251 --> 00:03:06,206
And He said, 
“So when I embrace you,

43
00:03:06,206 --> 00:03:09,112
it’s a like a mother with her …
I just …

44
00:03:09,112 --> 00:03:12,571
There’s no part of you 
that repulses me,

45
00:03:12,571 --> 00:03:15,249
in fact I enjoy 
every part of you.

46
00:03:15,338 --> 00:03:18,632
And that oozing from you 
to me is like, he says:

47
00:03:18,632 --> 00:03:23,114
‘chatuḥsam’: it means: 
sandalwood, a little camphor …

48
00:03:23,114 --> 00:03:25,875
like, a very divine mixture.

49
00:03:26,289 --> 00:03:29,179
He’s saying,
“That’s how it smells to me.”

50
00:03:30,787 --> 00:03:34,520
And that’s when the verse 
comes that says:

51
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:41,029
dīkṣā-kāle bhakta kare ātma-samarpaṇa
[Cc: 3.4.192]

52
00:03:41,064 --> 00:03:45,039
that when real dīkṣā is there,
ātma-samarpaṇa

53
00:03:45,039 --> 00:03:49,819
—when you’ve given yourself over
like a baby to its mother,

54
00:03:50,695 --> 00:03:53,602
you’ve given yourself
wholly over to Kṛṣṇa—

55
00:03:53,602 --> 00:03:58,202
he says ‘ātma-sam’—
they’re the same as me.

56
00:03:58,294 --> 00:04:01,298
That’s how I see it.
That’s how Kṛṣṇa sees it.

57
00:04:02,051 --> 00:04:07,271
That’s why we have to be very careful
about vaiṣṇava-aparādh

58
00:04:08,009 --> 00:04:11,697
for whom Kṛṣṇa 
has accepted as His own.

59
00:04:11,790 --> 00:04:17,937
Because they have potential, 
as Guru Mahārāj says, ‘adaptable’;

60
00:04:18,539 --> 00:04:27,130
they have a potential to realise 
the greatest thing possible,

61
00:04:27,370 --> 00:04:32,539
and that is 
immeasurably valuable.

62
00:04:33,179 --> 00:04:39,500
So to give someone that opportunity
is the ultimate genorosity,

63
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:48,829
magnanimity, mercy,
because they do have that capacity.

64
00:04:48,829 --> 00:04:53,049
They have the capacity
to express Kṛṣṇa-prema,

65
00:04:55,338 --> 00:05:00,369
of which nothing 
compares in value.

